settings.title: Grass Seed Calculator
settings.content:
Seeding a new lawn or overseeding an established one? Use our calculator to find out how much grass seed you’ll need for your project.*

This calculator is to be used as an estimating tool only.

Select a Growing Zone

We use growing zones to identify the best grass types for your geographic area. Use the Grass Seed Zone Map to identify your zone.

Select Grass Seed Type

Grass Seed Types

Bahia
Produces a low- maintenance, durable lawn. A deep root system provides excellent drought resistance.
Bermuda
Produces a medium green, drought-resistant lawn. Aggressively spreads to fill in bare spots.
Bluegrass
Produces a deep green, tightly knit and finely textured lawn. Self-spreads to fill in bare spots.
Centipede
Medium green, medium-width grass blades. Slow, self-spreading grass.
Kentucky 31
Produces a medium green, wide-bladed lawn. Drought resistant with good disease tolerance. Remains green all year round.
Ryegrass
Produces a dark green, thin-bladed lawn. One of the easiest grasses to establish.
Shade Mix
Attractive, thin- bladed turf. Grows best under dense trees and other shaded areas.
St. Augustine
Wide-bladed grass, available only as sprigs, plugs or sod.
Sun & Shade Mix
Produces a dark green, thin-bladed lawn and thrives in sunny and shady conditions. Ryegrass and perennial bluegrass mixed to grow well.
Tall Fescue
Dense, medium to dark green weed-resistant turf. Heat, drought, disease and insect resistant.
Zoysia
Dark green, thin, upright grass blades. Slow, self-spreading grass.

The spread rate for Bahia grass seed is 5 to 10 Bermuda grass seed is 2 to 3 (coated)/1 to 2 (raw) Bluegrass grass seed is 1 to 3 Centipede grass seed is .25 to .50 Kentucky 31 grass seed is 5 to 10 Ryegrass grass seed is 5 to 10 Shade Mix grass seed is 4 to 6 St. Augustine grass seed is 1 to 2 Sun & Shade Mix grass seed is 4 to 6 Tall Fescue grass seed is 5 to 10 Zoysia grass seed is 1 to 2 pounds per 1,000 square feet.

*Actual quantities may vary by application method and brand. Check product labels for spread rates. Grass seed estimates don’t apply to pastures.
